                    <Details>
                        <Detail SortOrder="1" TypeOfProgramAndActivitiesDetailsId="1778">
                            <FooterDetails>
                                <Email/>
                                <Footer/>
                                <WebAddress>https://www.mda.mil/about/about.html</WebAddress>
                            </FooterDetails>
                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The Missile Defense Agency's (MDA) mission is
                                                to establish and deploy a layered ballistic missile
                                                defense system to intercept missiles in all phases
                                                of their flight and against all ranges of threats.
                                                This capability will provide a defense of the United
                                                States, deployed forces, and allies. The MDA is
                                                under the authority, direction, and control of the
                                                Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition,
                                                Technology, and Logistics. It manages and directs
                                                DOD's ballistic missile defense acquisition programs
                                                and enables the Services to field elements of the
                                                overall system as soon as practicable. The MDA
                                                develops and tests technologies and, if necessary,
                                                uses prototype and test assets to provide early
                                                capability. Additionally, MDA improves the
                                                effectiveness of deployed capabilities by
                                                implementing new technologies as they become
                                                available or when the threat warrants an accelerated
                                                capability.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                    </Details>
                </Activity>
            </ProgramAndActivity>
